The paper deals with image geolocalization, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques to identify the location depicted in a photo. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for partitioning the earth into fine-grained output classes, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of multiple benchmark datasets, indicating a focus on evaluation and comparison, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to describe the proposed algorithm, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
